A would-be thief at a Manhattan Duane Reade used a hypodermic needle to try to stab the security guard who foiled the attempted robbery last weekend, police said. The suspect was caught on camera shoving items from the storeâ€™s refrigerated section into a shopping bag at the location on East 34 Street near Third Avenue in Murray Hill at about 10:15 a.m. Saturday, the NYPD said. When the man tried to flee with the stolen goods, he was approached by the security guard and the two got into a struggle, police said. At one point during the confrontation, the suspect pulled out the needle and tried to stab the worker, according to cops. The clash continued on for a brief time before the suspect left the store empty-handed, police said. He remained in the wind as of early Wednesday. The security guard suffered pain to his left hand, but refused medical attention.